Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to moderate turn. Clay fine pink-red; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Production date: 210 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Xenophantos. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0189.13.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0674)
